ice? What if the Scots Jacobites turn out to be the most radical, revolutionary party in early eighteenth-century British politics? Using newly discovered sources from the French and Scottish archives this exciting new book challenges our fundamental assumptions regarding the emergence of the fully British state in the early eighteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJacobites. 7aHISTORY / Europe / General.2bisacsh  aBritish history.  aFrench government.  aFrench grand strategy.  aJacobite Scotland.  aQueen Mary of Modena.  aScots Jacobite movement.  aScots noblewomen.  aclimactic moment.  ageopolitics.  ahistoriography.1 aSzechi, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978184779989040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847799890423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847799890/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  Manchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packageb2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles